Predicted changes in the primordial deuterium abundance, D/H, helium-4 abundance, Yp, lithium-7 abundance, Li7/H, and effective number of relatovisitic neutrino species (where applicable), Neff, as a function of a fractional variation in the input parameter p, with all other inputs held fixed at their fiducial values. The slope near the fiducial point defines the local logarithmic response ∂lnY/∂lnp used to build the sensitivity matrix and propagate theory uncertainties.
